  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Rinse the peas and set them aside.",
    "In a large saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add the peas, salt, and pepper, and cook for 2-3 minutes until they start to soften.",
    "Transfer the pea mixture to a baking dish.",
    "Drizzle the olive oil and infused oil over the peas.",
    "Sprinkle the Grana Padano cheese and breadcrumbs over the top.",
    "Bake for 15-20 minutes until the top is golden brown and the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
